column1: Subject: Labour, Employment, Wages and Productivity
Table Title: Employed Residents Aged 15 Years And Over By Industry And Age Group, (June), Annual

Residents comprise Singapore citizens and permanent residents.  Based on mid-year Labour Force Survey except for Census of Population 2000 and General Household Survey 2005.  To facilitate comparison with 2008, 2007 Labour Force Survey data have been adjusted based on Singapore Department of Statistics revised population estimates (released in February 2008) which exclude Singapore residents who have been away from Singapore for a continuous period of 12 months or longer.  Data from year 2020 are classified based on Singapore Standard Industrial Classification (SSIC) 2020.  Data before year 2020 which were coded based on earlier versions of the SSIC were mapped to SSIC 2020 as far as possible to facilitate data comparability.
All Industries (Employed Residents) -> Services -> Wholesale & Retail Trade (Thousand):
Data for 1991-1994 and 1996-1997 refers to wholesale, retail, hotels and restaurants.
All Industries (Employed Residents) -> Services -> Transportation & Storage (Thousand):
Data for 1991-1994, 1996-1999 and 2001-2004 refers to transport, storage and communications.
All Industries (Employed Residents) -> Services -> Financial & Insurance Services (Thousand):
Data for 1991-1994 and 1996-1997 refers to financial, insurance, real estate and business services.
Data includes Agriculture, Fishing, Quarrying, Utilities and Sewerage & Waste Management.
